Preheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6.Wash and dry the potatoes, but don't peel them. Cut the potatoes into large wedges and place into a bowl.Add the remaining ingredients to the bowl and mix well. Tip the potatoes onto a baking tray.Transfer the potatoes to the oven and bake until golden-brown and cooked all the way through (about 30 minutes).Serve the potatoes hot from the oven.